    "Fourth, due to how gradient-based methods estimate influence, highly influential instances can actually appear uninfluential at the end of training.",
    "Unlike static estimators, dynamic methods like TracIn may still be able to detect these instances.",
    "See Sect. 5.3 for more details.",
    "In terms of weaknesses, TracIn's theoretical motivation assumes stochastic gradient descent without momentum.",
    "However, momentum and adaptive optimization [e.g., Adam (Kingma & Ba, 2015) ] significantly accelerate model convergence (Qian, 1999; Duchi et al., 2011; Kingma & Ba, 2015)."
